## 📦 Variant examples

Use `.example-row.example-row--col` + `.size-row` for stacked label/component pairs:

```astro
<div class="example-row example-row--col">
  {[
    { prop: 'value1', label: 'Label for value1' },
    { prop: 'value2', label: 'Label for value2' },
  ].map(({ prop, label }) => (
    <div class="size-row">
      <span class="size-label">{label}</span>
      <Component prop={prop as any} />
    </div>
  ))}
</div>
```

Grid: `200px label | 1fr component`. Always `example-row--col` for variant lists.

---

## 📦 Combinations

Always include a live `.example-row` block showing actual component instances — not just text:

```astro
<h2 id="combinations">Combinations</h2>
<p>Short description of what pairs with what and why.</p>
<div class="example-row example-row--col">
  <div class="size-row">
    <span class="size-label">Context label</span>
    <Component prop="value" />
  </div>
  <div class="size-row">
    <span class="size-label">Another context</span>
    <Component prop="other" />
  </div>
</div>
```

